items.title: Square Root Day - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.htmlTitle: Square Root Day - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
Square Root Day is an unofficial holiday celebrated on days when both the day 
of the month and the month are the square root of the last two digits of the year.

items.title: Square root of 2 - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.htmlTitle: Square root of 2 - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
Geometrically the square root of 2 is the length of a diagonal across a square 
with sides of one unit of length; this follows from the Pythagorean theorem.
